## The experiment loop (template)

1. Note current git branch and commit.
2. Apply a **single** experimental change within allowed globs.
3. Commit with message `experiment: <short description>`.
4. Run `{{ execution.command }}` (respect timeout).
5. Parse **{{ measurement.primaryMetric.name }}** from output using the agreed extractor.
6. Append a row to `{{ provenance.resultsLog.path }}`.
7. If the metric improved per direction **{{ measurement.primaryMetric.direction }}**, keep the commit; otherwise revert per team policy.

